summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from the Weyerhaeuser Timber Co., a corporation, duly incorporated under the laws of the State of Washington, to the City of Seattle, dated the 12th day of July, in the year of our Lord one thousand nine hundred and ten, to certain tracts of lands situated in Sections Twenty-seven (27) and Twenty-three (23), Township twenty-three (23) North, Range eight (8) East, W. M. in King County, State of Washington.
